metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_BASE_THIS_RUN
metadata.comment: This staging table aggregates media player interactions within the current run to a pageview level that is considered a base level for media plays.

PLAY_ID.name: PLAY_ID
PLAY_ID.comment: The surrogate key generated from `page_view_id`, `player_id`, `media_label`, `media_type` and `media_player_type` to create a unique play event identifier.

PAGE_VIEW_ID.name: PAGE_VIEW_ID
PAGE_VIEW_ID.comment:
A UUID for each page view e.g. `c6ef3124-b53a-4b13-a233-0088f79dcbcb`.
If more than one page view IDs were tracked for a single play ID, the first page view ID is used.

PAGE_VIEW_ID_ARRAY.name: PAGE_VIEW_ID_ARRAY
PAGE_VIEW_ID_ARRAY.comment:
All page_view_ids that were tracked for a play_id.
A play_id may contain more than one page_view_id in case the video was played in picture-in-picture mode across multiple app pages/screens.

MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.name: MEDIA_IDENTIFIER
MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.comment: The surrogate key generated from `player_id`, `media_label`, `media_type` and `media_player_type` to create a unique media element identifier.

PLAYER_ID.name: PLAYER_ID
PLAYER_ID.comment: The HTML id attribute of the media content. It is the `player_id` in case of YouTube and `html_id` in case of HTML5.

MEDIA_LABEL.name: MEDIA_LABEL
MEDIA_LABEL.comment: The optional, human readable name given to tracked media content.

SESSION_IDENTIFIER.name: SESSION_IDENTIFIER
SESSION_IDENTIFIER.comment: The session identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to the media_session_id, or to page_view_id if the media session entity is not enabled.

APP_ID.name: APP_ID
APP_ID.comment: Application ID e.g. ‘angry-birds’ is used to distinguish different applications that are being tracked by the same Snowplow stack, e.g. production versus dev.

DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY.name: DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY
DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY.comment: All domain_sessionids seen for a play_id.

USER_IDENTIFIER.name: USER_IDENTIFIER
USER_IDENTIFIER.comment: The user identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to domain_userid.

USER_ID.name: USER_ID
USER_ID.comment: Unique ID set by business e.g. ‘jon.doe@email.com’

SOURCE_URL.name: SOURCE_URL
SOURCE_URL.comment: The url which shows the source of the media content. For YouTube it is the `url` context field, for HTML5 it is the `source_url` field.

DURATION_SECS.name: DURATION_SECS
DURATION_SECS.comment: Total length of media in seconds e.g. it's a 5:32 youtube video so the duration is 332 seconds.

MEDIA_TYPE.name: MEDIA_TYPE
MEDIA_TYPE.comment: The type of media content: video or audio.

MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE.name: MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE
MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE.comment: The combination of schema_name and schema_vendor coming from the specific media player context e.g. com.youtube-youtube, org.whatwg-media_element.

START_TSTAMP.name: START_TSTAMP
START_TSTAMP.comment: The `derived_tstamp` denoting the time when the event started.

END_TSTAMP.name: END_TSTAMP
END_TSTAMP.comment: The `derived_tstamp` denoting the time when the last media player event belonging to the specific level of aggregation (e.g.: page_view by media) started.

AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE.name: AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE
AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE.comment: Average playback rate (1 is normal speed).

PLAY_TIME_SECS.name: PLAY_TIME_SECS
PLAY_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds user spent playing content (excluding linear ads). If the media session entity is tracked with media events, the information is read from there. This is an accurate measurement provided by the tracker.

 This also counts playback of rewatched content (see `content_watched_secs` for a measurement without considering rewatched content).

If the media session entity is not tracked, the value is estimated. It is calculated using the percent_progress events that are fired during play. In case such an event is fired, it is assumed that the total section of the media in between the previous and current percent_progress is played through, even if the user seeks to another point in time within the audio / video. The more often these events are tracked (e.g. every 5% of the media's length) the more accurate the calculation becomes.

PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS.name: PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS
PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS.comment:
Total seconds user spent playing content on mute (excluding linear ads). If the media session entity is tracked with media events, the information is read from there. This is an accurate measurement provided by the tracker.

If the media session entity is not tracked, the value is estimated. It is based on the percent_progress event and whether the user played it on mute during this event or not.

PAUSED_TIME_SECS.name: PAUSED_TIME_SECS
PAUSED_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds user spent with paused content (excluding linear ads).

This information is provided by the tracker in the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

BUFFERING_TIME_SECS.name: BUFFERING_TIME_SECS
BUFFERING_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds that playback was buffering.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

ADS_TIME_SECS.name: ADS_TIME_SECS
ADS_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds that ads played.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

SEEKS.name: SEEKS
SEEKS.comment: The count of seek events within a certain aggregation level. The seek event occurs when a user moves/skips to a new position in the media content.

ADS.name: ADS
ADS.comment:
Number of ads played.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

ADS_CLICKED.name: ADS_CLICKED
ADS_CLICKED.comment:
Number of ads that the user clicked on.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

ADS_SKIPPED.name: ADS_SKIPPED
ADS_SKIPPED.comment:
Number of ads that the user skipped.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

AD_BREAKS.name: AD_BREAKS
AD_BREAKS.comment:
Number of ad breaks played.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

IS_PLAYED.name: IS_PLAYED
IS_PLAYED.comment: Pageviews with at least one play event.

IS_VALID_PLAY.name: IS_VALID_PLAY
IS_VALID_PLAY.comment: A boolean value to show whether the duration of the play (`play_time_secs`) is bigger than or equal to the variable given in `snowplow__valid_play_sec` (defaulted to 30).

IS_COMPLETE_PLAY.name: IS_COMPLETE_PLAY
IS_COMPLETE_PLAY.comment: A boolean value to show whether the total percentage played is bigger than or equal to the `snowplow__complete_play_rate` (defaulted to 0.99).

RETENTION_RATE.name: RETENTION_RATE
RETENTION_RATE.comment: The maximum percent progress reached before any seek event.

PERCENT_PROGRESS_REACHED.name: PERCENT_PROGRESS_REACHED
PERCENT_PROGRESS_REACHED.comment: An array of percent progresses reached by the user while playing the media. In case the same percentprogress event was fired during the same page_view (e.g. due to seeks to rewatch part of the video) the % is added to the array again. e.g. in case of percent_progress_reached = [10, 25, 25, 50, 75] the user replayed part of the media so that the percentprogress event fired twice at the 25% mark.

CONTENT_WATCHED_SECS.name: CONTENT_WATCHED_SECS
CONTENT_WATCHED_SECS.comment:
Total seconds of the content played. Each part of the content played is counted once (i.e., counts rewinding or rewatching the same content only once).

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

CONTENT_WATCHED_PERCENT.name: CONTENT_WATCHED_PERCENT
CONTENT_WATCHED_PERCENT.comment:
Percentage of the content played.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_MEDIA_STATS
metadata.comment: This derived table aggregates the pageview level interactions to show overall media stats.

MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.name: MEDIA_IDENTIFIER
MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.comment: The primary key of this table

PLAYER_ID.name: PLAYER_ID
PLAYER_ID.comment: The HTML id attribute of the media content. It is the `player_id` in case of YouTube and `html_id` in case of HTML5.

MEDIA_LABEL.name: MEDIA_LABEL
MEDIA_LABEL.comment: The optional, human readable name given to tracked media content.

DURATION_SECS.name: DURATION_SECS
DURATION_SECS.comment: Total length of media in seconds e.g. it's a 5:32 youtube video so the duration is 332 seconds.

MEDIA_TYPE.name: MEDIA_TYPE
MEDIA_TYPE.comment: The type of media content: video or audio.

MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE.name: MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE
MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE.comment: The combination of schema_name and schema_vendor coming from the specific media player context e.g. com.youtube-youtube, org.whatwg-media_element.

PLAY_TIME_MINS.name: PLAY_TIME_MINS
PLAY_TIME_MINS.comment: Calculated duration of play in minutes.  This also counts rewatched content (see `avg_content_watched_mins` for a measurement without considering rewatched content).

AVG_PLAY_TIME_MINS.name: AVG_PLAY_TIME_MINS
AVG_PLAY_TIME_MINS.comment:
Estimated average duration of plays in minutes. This also counts rewatched content (see `avg_content_watched_mins` for a measurement without considering rewatched content).

If the media session context entity is tracked with events, the information is taken from there which makes it more accurate since it is calculated on the tracker. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

AVG_CONTENT_WATCHED_MINS.name: AVG_CONTENT_WATCHED_MINS
AVG_CONTENT_WATCHED_MINS.comment:
Average duration of the content played in minutes. Each part of the content played is counted once (i.e., counts rewinding or rewatching the same content only once).

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

FIRST_PLAY.name: FIRST_PLAY
FIRST_PLAY.comment: The `derived_tstamp` of the beginning of the first play of a media element.

LAST_PLAY.name: LAST_PLAY
LAST_PLAY.comment: The `derived_tstamp` of the beginning of the last play of a media element.

PLAYS.name: PLAYS
PLAYS.comment: The number of pageviews with plays of any duration.

VALID_PLAYS.name: VALID_PLAYS
VALID_PLAYS.comment: The sum of all media plays that exceeds the minimum media length set within the variable `snowplow__valid_play_sec`, it is defaulted to 30 (seconds).

COMPLETE_PLAYS.name: COMPLETE_PLAYS
COMPLETE_PLAYS.comment: The number of plays where the total percentage played is bigger than or equal to the `snowplow__complete_play_rate`. Default is 0.99, meaning that 99% of the video being watched constitutes a complete play.

IMPRESSIONS.name: IMPRESSIONS
IMPRESSIONS.comment: The number of player instance (media sessions) where a media content was rendered regardless of whether the media was actually played or not.

AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE.name: AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE
AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE.comment: Average playback rate (1 is normal speed).

PLAY_RATE.name: PLAY_RATE
PLAY_RATE.comment: Total plays divided by impressions. Please note that, if the media session ID is not available, as the base for media plays is pageview / media_identifier, in case the same video is played multiple times within the same pageview, it will still count as one play.

COMPLETION_RATE_BY_PLAYS.name: COMPLETION_RATE_BY_PLAYS
COMPLETION_RATE_BY_PLAYS.comment: The number of complete plays divided by the number of pageviews with plays of any duration.

AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED.name: AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED
AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED.comment: Average of total play_time divided by the media duration.

AVG_RETENTION_RATE.name: AVG_RETENTION_RATE
AVG_RETENTION_RATE.comment: The maximum percent progress reached before any seek event.

LAST_BASE_TSTAMP.name: LAST_BASE_TSTAMP
LAST_BASE_TSTAMP.comment: The start_tstamp of the last processed page_view across all media_identifiers to be used as a lower limit for subsequent incremental runs.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_USER_STATS
metadata.comment: This table aggregates the session level stats to show user level media stats.

USER_IDENTIFIER.name: USER_IDENTIFIER
USER_IDENTIFIER.comment: The user identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to domain_userid.

FIRST_PLAY.name: FIRST_PLAY
FIRST_PLAY.comment: The `derived_tstamp` of the beginning of the first play of a media element.

LAST_PLAY.name: LAST_PLAY
LAST_PLAY.comment: The `derived_tstamp` of the beginning of the last play of a media element.

VIDEO_PLAYS.name: VIDEO_PLAYS
VIDEO_PLAYS.comment: The number of pageviews with video plays of any duration.

AUDIO_PLAYS.name: AUDIO_PLAYS
AUDIO_PLAYS.comment: The number of pageviews with audio plays of any duration.

VALID_VIDEO_PLAYS.name: VALID_VIDEO_PLAYS
VALID_VIDEO_PLAYS.comment: The sum of all video plays that exceed the limit set within the variable `snowplow__valid_play_sec`, it is defaulted to 30 seconds.

VALID_AUDIO_PLAYS.name: VALID_AUDIO_PLAYS
VALID_AUDIO_PLAYS.comment: The sum of all audio plays that exceeded the limit set within the variable `snowplow__valid_play_sec`, it is defaulted to 30 seconds.

COMPLETE_PLAYS.name: COMPLETE_PLAYS
COMPLETE_PLAYS.comment: The number of plays where the total percentage played is bigger than or equal to the `snowplow__complete_play_rate`. Default is 0.99, meaning that 99% of the video being watched constitutes a complete play.

SEEKS.name: SEEKS
SEEKS.comment: The count of seek events within a certain aggregation level. The seek event occurs when a user moves/skips to a new position in the media content.

PLAY_TIME_MINS.name: PLAY_TIME_MINS
PLAY_TIME_MINS.comment: Calculated duration of play in minutes.  This also counts rewatched content (see `avg_content_watched_mins` for a measurement without considering rewatched content).

AVG_SESSION_PLAY_TIME_MINS.name: AVG_SESSION_PLAY_TIME_MINS
AVG_SESSION_PLAY_TIME_MINS.comment: Estimated average duration of plays in seconds within a session.

AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED.name: AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED
AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED.comment: Average of total play_time divided by the media duration.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_MEDIA_AD_VIEWS_THIS_RUN
metadata.comment: This derived table aggregates information about ad views. Each ad view (a user viewing a single ad within a media playback) is represented using one row. The ad views aggregate information about the percentage progress of the ad viewed, whether it was skipped, clicked or completed. They also contain meta information about the played ads.

MEDIA_AD_VIEW_ID.name: MEDIA_AD_VIEW_ID
MEDIA_AD_VIEW_ID.comment: The primary key of this table

MEDIA_AD_ID.name: MEDIA_AD_ID
MEDIA_AD_ID.comment: Generated identifier that identifies an ad (identified using the ad_id) played with a specific media (identified using the media_identifier) and on a specific platform (based on the platform property).

MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.name: MEDIA_IDENTIFIER

MEDIA_LABEL.name: MEDIA_LABEL

USER_IDENTIFIER.name: USER_IDENTIFIER
USER_IDENTIFIER.comment: User ID set by Snowplow using 1st party cookie e.g. `bc2e92ec6c204a14`.

SESSION_IDENTIFIER.name: SESSION_IDENTIFIER

APP_ID.name: APP_ID

DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY.name: DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY

PLAY_ID.comment: The surrogate key generated from `page_view_id`, `player_id`, `media_label`, `media_type` and `media_player_type` to create a unique play event identifier.

AD_BREAK_ID.name: AD_BREAK_ID
AD_BREAK_ID.comment: An identifier for the ad break (reported in the ad_break context entity).

AD_BREAK_NAME.name: AD_BREAK_NAME
AD_BREAK_NAME.comment: Ad break name (e.g., pre-roll, mid-roll, and post-roll), reported in the ad_break context entity.

AD_BREAK_TYPE.name: AD_BREAK_TYPE
AD_BREAK_TYPE.comment: Type of ads within the break: linear (take full control of the video for a period of time), nonlinear (run concurrently to the video), companion (accompany the video but placed outside the player). Reported in the ad_break context entity.

AD_ID.name: AD_ID
AD_ID.comment: Unique identifier for the ad taken from the ad context entity.

NAME.name: NAME

CREATIVE_ID.name: CREATIVE_ID
CREATIVE_ID.comment: The ID of the ad creative taken from the ad context entity.

DURATION_SECS.name: DURATION_SECS
DURATION_SECS.comment: Length of the video ad in seconds as reported in the ad context entity.

POD_POSITION.name: POD_POSITION
POD_POSITION.comment: The position of the ad within the ad break, starting with 1 (reported in the ad context entity).

SKIPPABLE.name: SKIPPABLE
SKIPPABLE.comment: Indicating whether skip controls are made available to the end user (reported in the ad context entity).

CLICKED.name: CLICKED
CLICKED.comment: Whether the ad was clicked during this ad view.

SKIPPED.name: SKIPPED
SKIPPED.comment: Whether the ad was skipped during this ad view.

PERCENT_REACHED_25.name: PERCENT_REACHED_25
PERCENT_REACHED_25.comment: Number of times users reached 25% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_50.name: PERCENT_REACHED_50
PERCENT_REACHED_50.comment: Number of times users reached 50% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_75.name: PERCENT_REACHED_75
PERCENT_REACHED_75.comment: Number of times users reached 75% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_100.name: PERCENT_REACHED_100
PERCENT_REACHED_100.comment: Number of times users watched the whole ad (repeated views are counted as well).

VIEWED_AT.name: VIEWED_AT
VIEWED_AT.comment: Datetime when the ad was viewed.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_PLAYS_BY_PAGEVIEW
metadata.comment: This view removes impressions from the derived snowplow_media_player_base table for showing pageview level media play events. This means that only media player instances where a play event was tracked are kept (where `is_played` is true).

PLAY_ID.name: PLAY_ID
PLAY_ID.comment: The surrogate key generated from `page_view_id`, `player_id`, `media_label`, `media_type` and `media_player_type` to create a unique play event identifier.

PAGE_VIEW_ID.name: PAGE_VIEW_ID
PAGE_VIEW_ID.comment:
A UUID for each page view e.g. `c6ef3124-b53a-4b13-a233-0088f79dcbcb`.
If more than one page view IDs were tracked for a single play ID, the first page view ID is used.

PAGE_VIEW_ID_ARRAY.name: PAGE_VIEW_ID_ARRAY
PAGE_VIEW_ID_ARRAY.comment:
All page_view_ids that were tracked for a play_id.
A play_id may contain more than one page_view_id in case the video was played in picture-in-picture mode across multiple app pages/screens.

MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.name: MEDIA_IDENTIFIER
MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.comment: The surrogate key generated from `player_id`, `media_label`, `media_type` and `media_player_type` to create a unique media element identifier.

PLAYER_ID.name: PLAYER_ID
PLAYER_ID.comment: The HTML id attribute of the media content. It is the `player_id` in case of YouTube and `html_id` in case of HTML5.

MEDIA_LABEL.name: MEDIA_LABEL
MEDIA_LABEL.comment: The optional, human readable name given to tracked media content.

SESSION_IDENTIFIER.name: SESSION_IDENTIFIER
SESSION_IDENTIFIER.comment: The session identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to the media_session_id, or to page_view_id if the media session entity is not enabled.

APP_ID.name: APP_ID
APP_ID.comment: Application ID e.g. ‘angry-birds’ is used to distinguish different applications that are being tracked by the same Snowplow stack, e.g. production versus dev.

DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY.name: DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY
DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY.comment: All domain_sessionids seen for a play_id.

USER_IDENTIFIER.name: USER_IDENTIFIER
USER_IDENTIFIER.comment: The user identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to domain_userid.

USER_ID.name: USER_ID
USER_ID.comment: Unique ID set by business e.g. ‘jon.doe@email.com’

SOURCE_URL.name: SOURCE_URL
SOURCE_URL.comment: The url which shows the source of the media content. For YouTube it is the `url` context field, for HTML5 it is the `source_url` field.

DURATION_SECS.name: DURATION_SECS
DURATION_SECS.comment: Total length of media in seconds e.g. it's a 5:32 youtube video so the duration is 332 seconds.

MEDIA_TYPE.name: MEDIA_TYPE
MEDIA_TYPE.comment: The type of media content: video or audio.

MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE.name: MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE
MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE.comment: The combination of schema_name and schema_vendor coming from the specific media player context e.g. com.youtube-youtube, org.whatwg-media_element.

START_TSTAMP.name: START_TSTAMP
START_TSTAMP.comment: The `derived_tstamp` denoting the time when the event started.

END_TSTAMP.name: END_TSTAMP
END_TSTAMP.comment: The `derived_tstamp` denoting the time when the last media player event belonging to the specific level of aggregation (e.g.: page_view by media) started.

AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE.name: AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE
AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE.comment: Average playback rate (1 is normal speed).

PLAY_TIME_SECS.name: PLAY_TIME_SECS
PLAY_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds user spent playing content (excluding linear ads). If the media session entity is tracked with media events, the information is read from there. This is an accurate measurement provided by the tracker.

 This also counts playback of rewatched content (see `content_watched_secs` for a measurement without considering rewatched content).

If the media session entity is not tracked, the value is estimated. It is calculated using the percent_progress events that are fired during play. In case such an event is fired, it is assumed that the total section of the media in between the previous and current percent_progress is played through, even if the user seeks to another point in time within the audio / video. The more often these events are tracked (e.g. every 5% of the media's length) the more accurate the calculation becomes.

PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS.name: PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS
PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS.comment:
Total seconds user spent playing content on mute (excluding linear ads). If the media session entity is tracked with media events, the information is read from there. This is an accurate measurement provided by the tracker.

If the media session entity is not tracked, the value is estimated. It is based on the percent_progress event and whether the user played it on mute during this event or not.

PAUSED_TIME_SECS.name: PAUSED_TIME_SECS
PAUSED_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds user spent with paused content (excluding linear ads).

This information is provided by the tracker in the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

BUFFERING_TIME_SECS.name: BUFFERING_TIME_SECS
BUFFERING_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds that playback was buffering.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

ADS_TIME_SECS.name: ADS_TIME_SECS
ADS_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds that ads played.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

SEEKS.name: SEEKS
SEEKS.comment: The count of seek events within a certain aggregation level. The seek event occurs when a user moves/skips to a new position in the media content.

ADS.name: ADS
ADS.comment:
Number of ads played.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

ADS_CLICKED.name: ADS_CLICKED
ADS_CLICKED.comment:
Number of ads that the user clicked on.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

ADS_SKIPPED.name: ADS_SKIPPED
ADS_SKIPPED.comment:
Number of ads that the user skipped.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

AD_BREAKS.name: AD_BREAKS
AD_BREAKS.comment:
Number of ad breaks played.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

IS_PLAYED.name: IS_PLAYED
IS_PLAYED.comment: Pageviews with at least one play event.

IS_VALID_PLAY.name: IS_VALID_PLAY
IS_VALID_PLAY.comment: A boolean value to show whether the duration of the play (`play_time_secs`) is bigger than or equal to the variable given in `snowplow__valid_play_sec` (defaulted to 30).

IS_COMPLETE_PLAY.name: IS_COMPLETE_PLAY
IS_COMPLETE_PLAY.comment: A boolean value to show whether the total percentage played is bigger than or equal to the `snowplow__complete_play_rate` (defaulted to 0.99).

RETENTION_RATE.name: RETENTION_RATE
RETENTION_RATE.comment: The maximum percent progress reached before any seek event.

PERCENT_PROGRESS_REACHED.name: PERCENT_PROGRESS_REACHED
PERCENT_PROGRESS_REACHED.comment: An array of percent progresses reached by the user while playing the media. In case the same percentprogress event was fired during the same page_view (e.g. due to seeks to rewatch part of the video) the % is added to the array again. e.g. in case of percent_progress_reached = [10, 25, 25, 50, 75] the user replayed part of the media so that the percentprogress event fired twice at the 25% mark.

CONTENT_WATCHED_SECS.name: CONTENT_WATCHED_SECS
CONTENT_WATCHED_SECS.comment:
Total seconds of the content played. Each part of the content played is counted once (i.e., counts rewinding or rewatching the same content only once).

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

CONTENT_WATCHED_PERCENT.name: CONTENT_WATCHED_PERCENT
CONTENT_WATCHED_PERCENT.comment:
Percentage of the content played.

Calculated on the tracker and provided through the media session context entity. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_BASE_EVENTS_THIS_RUN
metadata.comment:
For any given run, this table contains all required events to be consumed by subsequent nodes in the Snowplow dbt media package. This is a cleaned, deduped dataset, containing all columns from the raw events table as well as having the `page_view_id` joined in from the page view context, and all of the fields parsed from the various media contexts.

**Note: This table should be used as the input to any custom modules that require event level data, rather than selecting straight from `atomic.events`**

COLLECTOR_TSTAMP.name: COLLECTOR_TSTAMP
COLLECTOR_TSTAMP.comment: Time stamp for the event recorded by the collector e.g. `2013-11-26 00:02:05`.

EVENT_ID.name: EVENT_ID
EVENT_ID.comment: A UUID for each event e.g. `c6ef3124-b53a-4b13-a233-0088f79dcbcb`.

USER_IDENTIFIER.name: USER_IDENTIFIER
USER_IDENTIFIER.comment: The user identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to domain_userid.

MEDIA_SESSION__MEDIA_SESSION_ID.name: MEDIA_SESSION__MEDIA_SESSION_ID
MEDIA_SESSION__MEDIA_SESSION_ID.comment: An identifier for the media session that is kept while the media content is played in the media player.

MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PLAYED.name: MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PLAYED
MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PLAYED.comment: Total seconds user spent playing content (excluding linear ads).

MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PLAYED_MUTED.name: MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PLAYED_MUTED
MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PLAYED_MUTED.comment: Total seconds user spent playing content on mute (excluding linear ads).

MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PAUSED.name: MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PAUSED
MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_PAUSED.comment: Total seconds user spent with paused content (excluding linear ads).

MEDIA_SESSION__CONTENT_WATCHED.name: MEDIA_SESSION__CONTENT_WATCHED
MEDIA_SESSION__CONTENT_WATCHED.comment: Total seconds of the content played. Each part of the content played is counted once (i.e., counts rewinding or rewatching the same content only once). Playback rate does not affect this value.

MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_BUFFERING.name: MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_BUFFERING
MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_BUFFERING.comment: Total seconds that playback was buffering during the session.

MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_SPENT_ADS.name: MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_SPENT_ADS
MEDIA_SESSION__TIME_SPENT_ADS.comment: Total seconds that ads played during the session.

MEDIA_SESSION__ADS_CLICKED.name: MEDIA_SESSION__ADS_CLICKED
MEDIA_SESSION__ADS_CLICKED.comment: Number of ads that the user clicked on.

MEDIA_SESSION__ADS_SKIPPED.name: MEDIA_SESSION__ADS_SKIPPED
MEDIA_SESSION__ADS_SKIPPED.comment: Number of ads that the user skipped.

MEDIA_SESSION__AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE.name: MEDIA_SESSION__AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE
MEDIA_SESSION__AVG_PLAYBACK_RATE.comment: Average playback rate (1 is normal speed).

MEDIA_AD__CREATIVE_ID.name: MEDIA_AD__CREATIVE_ID
MEDIA_AD__CREATIVE_ID.comment: The ID of the ad creative.

MEDIA_AD__POD_POSITION.name: MEDIA_AD__POD_POSITION
MEDIA_AD__POD_POSITION.comment: The position of the ad within the ad break, starting with 1.

MEDIA_AD__SKIPPABLE.name: MEDIA_AD__SKIPPABLE
MEDIA_AD__SKIPPABLE.comment: Indicating whether skip controls are made available to the end user.

MEDIA_AD_BREAK__NAME.name: MEDIA_AD_BREAK__NAME
MEDIA_AD_BREAK__NAME.comment: Ad break name (e.g., pre-roll, mid-roll, and post-roll), reported in the ad_break context entity.

MEDIA_AD_BREAK__BREAK_ID.name: MEDIA_AD_BREAK__BREAK_ID
MEDIA_AD_BREAK__BREAK_ID.comment: An identifier for the ad break (reported in the ad_break context entity).

MEDIA_AD_BREAK__BREAK_TYPE.name: MEDIA_AD_BREAK__BREAK_TYPE
MEDIA_AD_BREAK__BREAK_TYPE.comment: Type of ads within the break: linear (take full control of the video for a period of time), nonlinear (run concurrently to the video), companion (accompany the video but placed outside the player). Reported in the ad_break context entity.

AD_QUARTILE_EVENT__PERCENT_PROGRESS.name: AD_QUARTILE_EVENT__PERCENT_PROGRESS
AD_QUARTILE_EVENT__PERCENT_PROGRESS.comment: The percent of the way through the ad.

PAGE_VIEW_ID.name: PAGE_VIEW_ID
PAGE_VIEW_ID.comment:
A UUID for each page view e.g. `c6ef3124-b53a-4b13-a233-0088f79dcbcb`.
If more than one page view IDs were tracked for a single play ID, the first page view ID is used.

ORIGINAL_SESSION_IDENTIFIER.name: ORIGINAL_SESSION_IDENTIFIER
ORIGINAL_SESSION_IDENTIFIER.comment: The session identifier set by Snowplow using 1st party cookie. This is the domain_sessionid or session_id from the mobile session context.

MEDIA_LABEL.name: MEDIA_LABEL

DURATION_SECS.name: DURATION_SECS

PLAYER_CURRENT_TIME.name: PLAYER_CURRENT_TIME

IS_MUTED.name: IS_MUTED
IS_MUTED.comment: If the media is muted during the event that is fired.

PERCENT_PROGRESS.name: PERCENT_PROGRESS
PERCENT_PROGRESS.comment: The percent of the way through the media. It is based on either the percentprogress event that is fired at specific intervalls as defined during the tracker setup or the 'ended' event, which is equivalent to reaching 100% of the media's total duration (length). e.g. 25, meaning the user passed the 25% mark during play. PLAYER_ID.name: PLAYER_ID

MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE.name: MEDIA_PLAYER_TYPE

MEDIA_TYPE.name: MEDIA_TYPE
MEDIA_TYPE.comment: The type of media content: video or audio.

PLAYBACK_QUALITY.name: PLAYBACK_QUALITY
PLAYBACK_QUALITY.comment: Depending on the player it is either the playback quality field or the resolution.

EVENT_TYPE.name: EVENT_TYPE
EVENT_TYPE.comment: The type of event generated by the media player. e.g. 'ended', 'paused', 'playing'.

PLAY_TIME_SECS.comment:
Total seconds user spent playing content (excluding linear ads). If the media session entity is tracked with media events, the information is read from there. This is an accurate measurement provided by the tracker.

 This also counts playback of rewatched content (see `content_watched_secs` for a measurement without considering rewatched content).

In case such an event is fired, it is assumed that the total section of the media in between the previous and current percent_progress is played through, even if the user seeks to another point in time within the audio / video. The more often these events are tracked (e.g. every 5% of the media's length) the more accurate the calculation becomes.

PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS.name: PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS
PLAY_TIME_MUTED_SECS.comment:
Total seconds user spent playing content on mute (excluding linear ads). If the media session entity is tracked with media events, the information is read from there. This is an accurate measurement provided by the tracker.

If the media session entity is not tracked, the value is estimated. It is based on the percent_progress event and whether the user played it on mute during this event or not.

START_TSTAMP.comment: The `derived_tstamp` denoting the time when the event started.

EVENT_IN_SESSION_INDEX.name: EVENT_IN_SESSION_INDEX
EVENT_IN_SESSION_INDEX.comment: The index of the event in the corresponding session.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_MEDIA_AD_VIEWS
metadata.comment: This derived table aggregates media player interactions to a pageview level incrementally.

MEDIA_AD_VIEW_ID.name: MEDIA_AD_VIEW_ID
MEDIA_AD_VIEW_ID.comment: The primary key of this table

MEDIA_AD_ID.name: MEDIA_AD_ID
MEDIA_AD_ID.comment: Generated identifier that identifies an ad (identified using the ad_id) played with a specific media (identified using the media_identifier) and on a specific platform (based on the platform property).

MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.name: MEDIA_IDENTIFIER
MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.comment: The surrogate key generated from `player_id`, `media_label`, `media_type` and `media_player_type` to create a unique media element identifier.

MEDIA_LABEL.name: MEDIA_LABEL
MEDIA_LABEL.comment: The optional, human readable name given to tracked media content.

USER_IDENTIFIER.name: USER_IDENTIFIER
USER_IDENTIFIER.comment: The user identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to domain_userid.

SESSION_IDENTIFIER.name: SESSION_IDENTIFIER
SESSION_IDENTIFIER.comment: The session identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to the media_session_id, or to page_view_id if the media session entity is not enabled.

APP_ID.name: APP_ID
APP_ID.comment: Application ID e.g. ‘angry-birds’ is used to distinguish different applications that are being tracked by the same Snowplow stack, e.g. production versus dev.

DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY.name: DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY
DOMAIN_SESSIONID_ARRAY.comment: All domain_sessionids seen for a play_id.

USER_ID.name: USER_ID
USER_ID.comment: Unique ID set by business e.g. ‘jon.doe@email.com’

PLAY_ID.name: PLAY_ID
PLAY_ID.comment: The surrogate key generated from `page_view_id`, `player_id`, `media_label`, `media_type` and `media_player_type` to create a unique play event identifier.

AD_BREAK_ID.name: AD_BREAK_ID
AD_BREAK_ID.comment: An identifier for the ad break (reported in the ad_break context entity).

AD_BREAK_NAME.name: AD_BREAK_NAME
AD_BREAK_NAME.comment: Ad break name (e.g., pre-roll, mid-roll, and post-roll), reported in the ad_break context entity.

AD_BREAK_TYPE.name: AD_BREAK_TYPE
AD_BREAK_TYPE.comment: Type of ads within the break: linear (take full control of the video for a period of time), nonlinear (run concurrently to the video), companion (accompany the video but placed outside the player). Reported in the ad_break context entity.

AD_ID.name: AD_ID
AD_ID.comment: Unique identifier for the ad taken from the ad context entity.

NAME.name: NAME
NAME.comment: Friendly name of the ad taken from the ad context entity.

CREATIVE_ID.name: CREATIVE_ID
CREATIVE_ID.comment: The ID of the ad creative taken from the ad context entity.

DURATION_SECS.name: DURATION_SECS
DURATION_SECS.comment: Length of the video ad in seconds as reported in the ad context entity.

POD_POSITION.name: POD_POSITION
POD_POSITION.comment: The position of the ad within the ad break, starting with 1 (reported in the ad context entity).

SKIPPABLE.name: SKIPPABLE
SKIPPABLE.comment: Indicating whether skip controls are made available to the end user (reported in the ad context entity).

CLICKED.name: CLICKED
CLICKED.comment: Whether the ad was clicked during this ad view.

SKIPPED.name: SKIPPED
SKIPPED.comment: Whether the ad was skipped during this ad view.

PERCENT_REACHED_25.name: PERCENT_REACHED_25
PERCENT_REACHED_25.comment: Number of times users reached 25% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_50.name: PERCENT_REACHED_50
PERCENT_REACHED_50.comment: Number of times users reached 50% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_75.name: PERCENT_REACHED_75
PERCENT_REACHED_75.comment: Number of times users reached 75% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_100.name: PERCENT_REACHED_100
PERCENT_REACHED_100.comment: Number of times users watched the whole ad (repeated views are counted as well).

VIEWED_AT.name: VIEWED_AT
VIEWED_AT.comment: Datetime when the ad was viewed.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_BASE_QUARANTINED_SESSIONS
metadata.comment:
This table contains any sessions that have been quarantined. Sessions are quarantined once they exceed the maximum allowed session length, defined by `snowplow__max_session_days`.
Once quarantined, no further events from these sessions will be processed. Events up until the point of quarantine remain in your derived tables.
The reason for removing long sessions is to reduce table scans on both the events table and all derived tables. This improves performance greatly.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_SESSION_STATS
metadata.comment: This table aggregates the base level plays to show session level media stats.

USER_IDENTIFIER.name: USER_IDENTIFIER
USER_IDENTIFIER.comment: The user identifier as defined in your project variables. Default to domain_userid.

IMPRESSIONS.name: IMPRESSIONS
IMPRESSIONS.comment: The number of player instance (media sessions) where a media content was rendered regardless of whether the media was actually played or not.

VIDEOS_PLAYED.name: VIDEOS_PLAYED
VIDEOS_PLAYED.comment: The distinct number of videos that were played during a session.

AUDIO_PLAYED.name: AUDIO_PLAYED
AUDIO_PLAYED.comment: The distinct number of audio files that were played during a session.

VIDEO_PLAYS.name: VIDEO_PLAYS
VIDEO_PLAYS.comment: The number of pageviews with video plays of any duration.

AUDIO_PLAYS.name: AUDIO_PLAYS
AUDIO_PLAYS.comment: The number of pageviews with audio plays of any duration.

VALID_VIDEO_PLAYS.name: VALID_VIDEO_PLAYS
VALID_VIDEO_PLAYS.comment: The sum of all video plays that exceed the limit set within the variable `snowplow__valid_play_sec`, it is defaulted to 30 seconds.

VALID_AUDIO_PLAYS.name: VALID_AUDIO_PLAYS
VALID_AUDIO_PLAYS.comment: The sum of all audio plays that exceeded the limit set within the variable `snowplow__valid_play_sec`, it is defaulted to 30 seconds.

START_TSTAMP.name: START_TSTAMP
START_TSTAMP.comment: The `derived_tstamp` denoting the time when the event started.

END_TSTAMP.name: END_TSTAMP
END_TSTAMP.comment: The `derived_tstamp` denoting the time when the last media player event belonging to the specific level of aggregation (e.g.: page_view by media) started.

SEEKS.name: SEEKS
SEEKS.comment: The count of seek events within a certain aggregation level. The seek event occurs when a user moves/skips to a new position in the media content.

PLAY_TIME_MINS.name: PLAY_TIME_MINS
PLAY_TIME_MINS.comment: Calculated duration of play in minutes.  This also counts rewatched content (see `avg_content_watched_mins` for a measurement without considering rewatched content).

PLAY_TIME_MUTED_MINS.name: PLAY_TIME_MUTED_MINS
PLAY_TIME_MUTED_MINS.comment: Calculated duration of muted play in minutes. It is based on the percent_progress event and whether the user played it on mute during this event or not.

AVG_PLAY_TIME_MINS.name: AVG_PLAY_TIME_MINS
AVG_PLAY_TIME_MINS.comment:
Estimated average duration of plays in minutes. This also counts rewatched content (see `avg_content_watched_mins` for a measurement without considering rewatched content).

If the media session context entity is tracked with events, the information is taken from there which makes it more accurate since it is calculated on the tracker. If the media session entity is not tracked (when using our older tracking plugins or when it is disabled on the tracker), this property will be null.

AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED.name: AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED
AVG_PERCENT_PLAYED.comment: Average of total play_time divided by the media duration.

COMPLETE_PLAYS.name: COMPLETE_PLAYS
COMPLETE_PLAYS.comment: The number of plays where the total percentage played is bigger than or equal to the `snowplow__complete_play_rate`. Default is 0.99, meaning that 99% of the video being watched constitutes a complete play.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_MEDIA_ADS
metadata.comment: This derived table aggregates information about ads. Each row represents one ad played within a certain media on a certain platform. Stats about the number of ad clicks, progress reached and more are calculated as total values but also as counts of unique users (identified using `user_identifier`).

MEDIA_AD_ID.name: MEDIA_AD_ID
MEDIA_AD_ID.comment: The primary key of this table

MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.name: MEDIA_IDENTIFIER
MEDIA_IDENTIFIER.comment: The surrogate key generated from `player_id`, `media_label`, `media_type` and `media_player_type` to create a unique media element identifier.

MEDIA_LABEL.name: MEDIA_LABEL
MEDIA_LABEL.comment: The optional, human readable name given to tracked media content.

AD_ID.name: AD_ID
AD_ID.comment: Unique identifier for the ad taken from the ad context entity.

NAME.name: NAME
NAME.comment: Friendly name of the ad taken from the ad context entity.

CREATIVE_ID.name: CREATIVE_ID
CREATIVE_ID.comment: The ID of the ad creative taken from the ad context entity.

DURATION_SECS.name: DURATION_SECS
DURATION_SECS.comment: Total length of media in seconds e.g. it's a 5:32 youtube video so the duration is 332 seconds.

SKIPPABLE.name: SKIPPABLE
SKIPPABLE.comment: Indicating whether skip controls are made available to the end user (reported in the ad context entity).

POD_POSITION.name: POD_POSITION
POD_POSITION.comment: The position of the ad within the ad break, starting with 1 (reported in the ad context entity).

VIEWS.name: VIEWS
VIEWS.comment: Number of total views on the ad (repeated views are counted as well).

CLICKED.name: CLICKED
CLICKED.comment: Whether the ad was clicked during this ad view.

SKIPPED.name: SKIPPED
SKIPPED.comment: Whether the ad was skipped during this ad view.

PERCENT_REACHED_25.name: PERCENT_REACHED_25
PERCENT_REACHED_25.comment: Number of times users reached 25% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_50.name: PERCENT_REACHED_50
PERCENT_REACHED_50.comment: Number of times users reached 50% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_75.name: PERCENT_REACHED_75
PERCENT_REACHED_75.comment: Number of times users reached 75% of the ad playback (repeated views are counted as well).

PERCENT_REACHED_100.name: PERCENT_REACHED_100
PERCENT_REACHED_100.comment: Number of times users watched the whole ad (repeated views are counted as well).

VIEWS_UNIQUE.name: VIEWS_UNIQUE
VIEWS_UNIQUE.comment: Number of users that viewed the ad (identified by their user_identifier).

CLICKED_UNIQUE.name: CLICKED_UNIQUE
CLICKED_UNIQUE.comment: Number of users that clicked on the ad (identified by their user_identifier).

SKIPPED_UNIQUE.name: SKIPPED_UNIQUE
SKIPPED_UNIQUE.comment: Number of users that skipped the ad (identified by their user_identifier).

PERCENT_REACHED_25_UNIQUE.name: PERCENT_REACHED_25_UNIQUE
PERCENT_REACHED_25_UNIQUE.comment: Number of users that watched 25% of the ad (identified by their user_identifier).

PERCENT_REACHED_50_UNIQUE.name: PERCENT_REACHED_50_UNIQUE
PERCENT_REACHED_50_UNIQUE.comment: Number of users that watched 50% of the ad (identified by their user_identifier).

PERCENT_REACHED_75_UNIQUE.name: PERCENT_REACHED_75_UNIQUE
PERCENT_REACHED_75_UNIQUE.comment: Number of users that watched 75% of the ad (identified by their user_identifier).

PERCENT_REACHED_100_UNIQUE.name: PERCENT_REACHED_100_UNIQUE
PERCENT_REACHED_100_UNIQUE.comment: Number of users that watched 100% of the ad (identified by their user_identifier).

FIRST_VIEW.name: FIRST_VIEW
FIRST_VIEW.comment: Datetime of the first ad view.

LAST_VIEW.name: LAST_VIEW
LAST_VIEW.comment: Datetime of the last ad view.

metadata.name: SNOWPLOW_MEDIA_PLAYER_PIVOT_BASE
metadata.comment: This helper table serves as a base to calculate percent_progress based fields as well as the play_time metrics (by calculating the weight attributed to a percent progress being reached).

PERCENT_PROGRESS.name: PERCENT_PROGRESS
PERCENT_PROGRESS.comment: The percent of the way through the media. It is based on either the percentprogress event that is fired at specific intervalls as defined during the tracker setup or the 'ended' event, which is equivalent to reaching 100% of the media's total duration (length). e.g. 25, meaning the user passed the 25% mark during play. It does not mean the user watched all the content in between two percentprogress marks, unless there is no seek events happening within the same page_view (`snowplow_media_player_base`).

WEIGHT_RATE.name: WEIGHT_RATE
WEIGHT_RATE.comment: The weight given for each percent progress reached used for the calculation of the play_time_sec_estimated field. It is based on the difference of the current and preciding percent_progress rate.
